,Recommended,323670,26577755,"Posted: 13 November, 2016",all,Timji,"After almost 2h of playtime, I managed to beat all cups in 50cc (didn't play mirror yet). Here are my first impressions:+ It captures the feel and look of Super Mario Kart pretty well!+ Nice character and track variety+ you have multiple objectives in a race. Get first, collect the mushroom and collect a specific amount of money during the race. This is optional and raises the rank you earn at the end of the cup+ All the game modes you expect from Mario Kart are there, GP, Time Trial, Battle, Versus, ...+ the music is awesome!- the tracks are super colorful and full of hidden ways, items and other things. You feel really lost and need to learn every track before being able to get first everywhere- the developers really overdid it in terms of shortcuts. On some tracks, you can just use one shortcut after another until the end of the lap. Feels like every curve has 2 ways to drive it. Because of that you never know if you're driving the correct way. It's a bit too much- some soundeffects are really loud- drifting feels very unusual and needs some time to get it right. Doesn't feel as natural as Mario Kart at the beginningOverall I'm enjoying this game a lot. Most of my cons can be solved by the player by simply learning the tracks and the controls. Which is OK for a singleplayer game, but I feel like a Mario Kart-clone needs a better accessablity for new players.It doesn't really feel like an early access title to me, but it's strange that (at this moment) half of the tracks have no game references and are just colorful tracks.I also learned about many other promising indie titles with this game.I can definitely recommend this game!"
